1 A BILL for an Act to amend and reenact sections 43-28-03 and 43-28-18.2 of the North Dakota
2 Century Code, relating to members of the state board of dental examiners and an individual's
3 ability to file a complaint.
4 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATIVE ASSEMBLY OF NORTH DAKOTA:
5 SECTION 1. AMENDMENT. Section 43-28-03 of the North Dakota Century Code is
6 amended and reenacted as follows:
7 43-28-03. State board of dental examiners - Members - Appointment - Terms of office -
8 Oath - Vacancies.
9 1. The state board of dental examiners consists of nineeleven members appointed by the
10 governor. The membership of the board must include six:
11 a. Six dentist members, at least one of whom is a board-eligible or board-certified
12 oral and maxillofacial surgeon; one
13 b. One dental hygienist member; one
14 c. One dental assistant member; and one
15 d. Three independent consumer membermembers.
16 2. Appointment to the board is for a term of five years, with terms of office arranged so
17 no more than two terms expire on March sixteenth of each year. Each member of the
18 board shall hold office until a successor is appointed and qualified. An individual
19 appointed to the board qualifies by taking the oath required of civil officers. A member
20 may not serve more than ten years or two 5-year terms of office. If a member of the
21 board is absent from two consecutive regular meetings, the board may declare a
22 vacancy to exist. All vacancies on the board must be filled by the governor by
23 appointment.
