1 SECTION 2. AMENDMENT. Section 43-28-18.2 of the North Dakota Century Code is
2 amended and reenacted as follows:
3 43-28-18.2. Disciplinary procedure.
4 1. A personAn individual may file a written and signed complaint with the board alleging a
5 dentist engaged in conduct identified as grounds for disciplinary action under section
6 43-28-18. The board may also initiate a complaint and investigation on the board's
7 motion.
8 2. The board mayshall direct a complaint committee to investigate a complaint and
9 recommend whether the board should initiate a disciplinary action against the dentist.
10 3. The board or complaint committee shall notify the dentist of the complaint, and require
11 a written response from the dentist. If the complaint was initiated by an individual, that
12 individual must receive a copy of the dentist's response. The board or complaint
13 committee may examine and copy records, including patient records, examine
14 witnesses, obtain expert opinions, require the dentist to be physically or mentally
15 examined, or both, by qualified professionals selected by the board, and take any
16 other action necessary to investigate the complaint. A request by the board or
17 complaint committee is authorized to disclose patient information and records to the
18 board or complaint committee. Patient information and records disclosed to the board
19 or complaint committee are confidential. The dentist shall cooperate with the board or
20 the complaint committee in the investigation, including responding promptly and
21 completely to a request or requirement.
22 4. The complaint, response, and any record received by the board in investigating the
23 complaint are exempt records, as defined in section 44-04-17.1, until the board
24 determines to proceed with a disciplinary action.
25 5. The board shall determine if there is a reasonable basis to believe the dentist engaged
26 in conduct identified as grounds for disciplinary action under section 43-28-18. If the
27 board determines there is not a reasonable basis to believe, the board shall notify the
28 complainant and the dentist. If the board determines there is a reasonable basis to
29 believe, the board shall proceed with a disciplinary action in accordance with chapter
30 28-32.
